Aux:TextAnnotations.Aux:document_text: EDUVENTURES Membership Agreement October 3, 2008 The Tennessee Board of Regents Eduventures Learning Collaboratives Eduventures Learning Collaboratives are member-based research consortiums designed to help their memberships identify best management practices, benchmark performance, and improve the functioning of core processes across higher education. Each Collaborative is based on a continuum of services that includes multiple Collaborative Research studies, highly structured Campus Visits, access to our extraordinary group of industry analysts for specific inquiries and analysis, and various opportunities to connect with fellow professionals through annual Collaborative meetings, roundtables, and conferences. Proposed Business Relationship Eduventures proposes that The Tennessee Board of Regents join the Eduventures Online Higher Education Learning Collaborative (OHE-LC), on the following terms: Fee $24,750* *Note: The fee is discounted from the regular annual subscription fee of $27,500. The discounted fee is available until October 30, 2008. Term The ‘Term” of this membership agreement is 14 months, and shall begin upon The Tennessee Board of Regents’ signature of this agreement. Online Higher Education Learning Collaborative Eduventures will provide The Tennessee Board of Regents with access to the following services during the membership term: • OHE-LC Research Library: o Collaborative Research o Custom Analysis o Member Roundtable and Annual Member Meeting Resources • OHE-LC Forthcoming Research Deliverables: o Collaborative Research o Custom Analysis* ■ Custom Inquiry ■ Custom Research Reports ■ Membership Q&A • OHE-LC Implementation Support: o Analyst Discussions o Member Roundtables o Annual Member Meeting o Annual Campus Visit ♦Custom Analysis is available as needed, but we ask th at members limit their requests to one engagement at a time. There are no additional charges for access to our staff time for Custom Analysis; however, direct expenses (e.g., commercial databases and other third- party services) will be passed along to members at cost. Intellectual Property Eduventures Learning Collaborative membership provides The Tennessee Board of Regents with access to Eduventures Learning Collaborative research and restarch services for the Term. During this time, Eduventures Learning Collaborative research is available to The Tennessee Board of Regents, but remains the property of Eduventures and may not be redistributed by The Tennessee Board of Regents in any form without Eduventures’ prior written permission. Confidentiality The success of the Learning Collaborative depends upon information-sharing among its members. Learning Collaborative members are encouraged to share relevant experience and data as freely as possible. Upon request, Eduventures will remove identifying information from any material deemed sensitive by The Tennessee Board of Regents. Eduventures also understands that some of the information provided to us must be maintained in strict confidence. Maintaining the confidentiality of your proprietary information is important to Eduventures. Accordingly, you may request in writing that certain information you disclose to Eduventures be treated confidentially, and Eduventures agrees that it will not use or disclose such information except as required by law or as required to perform its services for you. You agree that Eduventures may use and disclose any aggregated, non-personally identifiable data, information, and knowledge that it creates and/or that results from the services being provided to you pursuant to this Agreement. Payment Terms An invoice will be sent upon receipt of this signed membership agreement. Payment is due 30 days from date of invoice.
